Kenya's deputy environment minister, Maathai, spearheaded a successful campaign to reduce plastic bag usage by 90% in just a year.
The government allocated funds from a plastic bag tax for environmental initiatives.
The United Nations Environment Programme urged Kenya to ban plastic bags, citing health risks.
San Francisco proposed a fee on grocery bags to curb plastic waste.
Rwanda and Uganda are also taking steps to ban plastic bags.
The issue of plastic pollution is a global concern, with efforts to promote eco-friendly alternatives and recycling initiatives underway in East Africa.
